messages.message:
Hi Team, Paychex is facing an issue when using ib_table_extractor_v2 package in the solution we delivered to them. They are able to build the ibflowbin from the ibflow file and able to successfully run the ibflowbin file without any issues. But when they run the ibflow from the flow editor they are getting the following error. ```Error running Flow: {"readyState":4,"responseText":" 502 Bad Gateway

502 Bad Gateway

nginx
","status":502,"statusText":"Bad Gateway"} ``` They raised the support ticker here. (https://instabase.zendesk.com/agent/tickets/3790) logs related to the issue too attached to the ticket. Instabase team given the resolution to increase the memory and CPU on their environment, but they could able to fix this issue without needing to increase the resources by pushing the decrypted version of the ib_table_extractor_v2 package. ib_table_extractor_v2 team mentioned that we have to share only encrypted version of the package, but they are able to get the decrypted version of the code just by extracting the ibsolution file we shared with them. 1. What is the solution for fixing the issue of running the solution on flow editor without the need for having the decrypted version of the package?. 2. If the solution is encrypted, how they are able to get the decrypted version of the code just by extracting it? cc: @Venkatesh @Balaram @Piyush @Veera
@Venkatesh Whom should this ticket be sent to since its open for almost a month

Hey Piyush. I think this is more of an encryption issue. To provide more context, this is the package.json for the package

https://instabase.com/apps/text-editor/ib_solutions/solutions/fs/Instabase%20Drive/pre-built/ib_table_extractor_v2/package/package.json

Furthermore, I tried manually extracting from the ibsolution. The src code seems to be encrypted.

cc: @Vasu
@Murali mentioned (and correct me if i misunderstood) that Paychex was able to decrypt this at their end and use
which they shouldn't be able to. If we can have more info on how they did this, it may help
Developer from Paychex mentioned that he just tried extracting it and no other tools he used for it.
I can ask him to present me the way he did it in tomorrows call.
